reviews.text:
The best way to understand the ways of living of a country is going to visit their local market; not chain supermarkets! Particularly to food lover, St. Josep is an excellent place to see why Spanish cuisine is so nice!

The following probably are good purchase from St. Josep for your kitchen at home if you enjoy cooking and eating:
1. Dried tomatoes and other fruits like figs (good for spaghetti and bakery);
2. Herbs especially saffron (expensive in Asia but cheap in Europe local market; very good for seafood);
3. Iberico ham (must must buy!! Good for pairing with wine and sweet melon; of course, for paella too).

There are restaurants and bars inside the market too; using fresh ingredients to cook. Don't miss it!
